{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a3f81c2e-7b44-4d92-8e3f-1d5f9c6a0e47",
    "name": "ETH-Liq-LTV-Coll1-1week-hourly",
    "description": "ACTUS DeFi ETH 1-week loan: COMPETING BEHAVIORAL RISKS simulation — HOURLY granularity.\n\nTWO behavioral models run simultaneously:\n  1. TwoDimensionalPrepaymentModel — voluntary rate-driven deleveraging\n     (spread × age surface, daily checks = 7 check points over 1 week)\n  2. CollateralLTVModel — protocol-enforced LTV-driven liquidation\n     (hourly monitoring = 168 check times over 7 days)\n\nScenario: Monotonic decline with intraday volatility\n  ETH: $2,410 → $2,280 (~5.4% weekly decline, with hourly noise)\n     Based on historical ETH bear-market intraday volatility pattern\n  Rate: 6.10% → 6.75% (gradual hourly rise)\n     Derived from the mid-period values of the 30-day base simulation\n  Collateral: 3.0 ETH, initial LTV = 69.3%  ($5000 / (3 × $2410))\n\nHourly index data: 169 data points each (00:00 on day 1 → 00:00 on day 8)\nHourly LTV monitoring: 168 times (every hour from day 1 01:00 → day 8 00:00)\nPrepayment checks: 7 daily checkpoints (one per day at 00:00)\nRate resets: hourly (cycle PT1HL1)\n\nKey LTV thresholds (Aave V3 calibrated):\n  ltvThreshold  = 75%  → partial repay to target 65%\n  liquidation   = 82.5% → full liquidation\n  LTV hits 75%   when ETH ≈ $2,222 (notional = $5,000 after zero prepayments)\n  LTV hits 82.5% when ETH ≈ $2,020\n\nScholarly Basis:\n  - Deng, Quigley & Van Order (2000), Econometrica: Competing risks framework\n  - Schwartz & Torous (1989, 1993): Rate-driven prepayment modeling\n  - Qin et al. (2021): DeFi liquidation mechanisms & thresholds\n  - Heimbach & Huang (2024), BIS WP 1171: DeFi leverage & voluntary buffers\n  - Lehar & Parlour (2022), BIS WP 1062: Systemic fragility, cascades\n  - Sadeghi (2025): Liquidation dynamics & transaction fees\n  - Aspris & Svec (2025): Skilled vs unskilled DeFi risk management\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
